d constraints of time and personnel, the emotional landscape, the intimate ethnographic settings and Andean people, the socio-politics, the difficult decisions and, especially, the role that ambiguity plays in determining archaeological meanings. Gero’s unique approach offers a new model for the site report as she masterfully demonstrates how the decisions made in conducting any scientific undertaking play a fundamental role in shaping the knowledge produced in that project.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aArchaeologyxFieldwork. 0aCommunity archaeologyzArgentina. 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zArgentina. 0aIndians of South AmericazArgentinazCatamarca (Province)xAntiquities. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Archaeology.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/77201440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477303948423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477303948/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK